Australia's **Superannuation Guarantee (SG) rate** increased to 12% from 1 July 2025. For a worker earning $95,000, this means the employer contributes $11,400 per year into super — on top of any salary sacrifice contributions.

Starting at age 35 with $85,000 in super and a $95,000 salary, you could accumulate approximately **$1.28 million** by retirement at 67, assuming 7% annual investment return. ASFA estimates a comfortable retirement requires $595,000 (single) or $690,000 (couple) in 2025 dollars — use this calculator to see if you are on track.
